title: `$h_t_m_l::apart()`
description: Extract HTML markup into PHP array.
...

~~~ .php.xmp
HTML::apart($input, $eval = true);
~~~

**Example:**

~~~ .php
$test = HTML::apart('<div class="main p" id="main">Content goes here…</div>');
~~~

Result:

~~~ .php
$test = [
    0 => 'div',
    1 => 'Content goes here…',
    2 => [
        'class' => 'main p'
        'class[]' => ['main', 'p'],
        'id' => 'main'
    ]
];
~~~